<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-046-552  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 046 552.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 10 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hitachi upgrades color palette LSI. (large scale integration chip)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Yazawa, Naoyuki.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hitachi Ltd. (product enhancement).andO;Topic:     Semiconductor industryEnhancementsLarge-Scale IntegrationSemiconductors.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>HITACHI UPGRADES COLOR PALETTE LSI TOKYO, JAPAN, 1989 OCT 3 (NB) -- Hitachihas developed an LSI (large- scale integration) chip based on IBM's VGA(video graphics array) color display standard, and is now shipping samples.andM;The LSI, called Color Palette LSI &quot;HD153110,&quot; is capable of displaying 16.77million colors simultaneously with its three channel, 8-bit digital analogconverter.andP;  Each RGB (red, green and blue) has 256 shades and these colorcombinations account for 16.77 million colors to display photo-realisticcolor images.andM;The new product is the upgraded version of its four and six-bit ColorPalette, but can be implemented without any change on software and systemswith the mode converter.andP;  Also, the new LSI has a digital output terminal forcolor liquid crystal display units.andM;The power consumption of the chip is 650 milliwatts and performs at 50 or 65megahertz of clock frequency.andM;(Naoyuki Yazawa/19891005)</TEXT></DOC>